<note class="safety-alert" id="note-00007">
<title>Beers Criteria<sup>&#174;</sup></title>
<para id="para-00031">Sedative-hypnotics should be avoided in <term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00066">older adults</term> (age 65 or older) because of associated risks including memory problems, drowsiness, increased risk of falls, and increased risk of having a motor vehicle collision.</para>
<para id="para-00032">(Source: Lee &amp; Green, 2019)</para>
</note>
</section>
