<glossary>
<definition id="def-00001"><term>angioedema</term> <meaning>fluid buildup in the deeper layers of the skin causing edema; considered a type of allergic reaction</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00002"><term>anterograde amnesia</term> <meaning>short-term memory loss</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00003"><term>anxiety</term> <meaning>a feeling of nervousness, apprehension, and/or worry about a future threat</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00004"><term>anxiolytics</term> <meaning>drugs that treat anxiety</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00005"><term>paradoxical medication effects</term> <meaning>when a medication causes an effect opposite to its intended outcome</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00006"><term>sedative-hypnotic</term> <meaning>class of drugs used to induce or maintain sleep</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00007"><term>sleep latency</term> <meaning>the amount of time it takes a person to fall asleep once they go to bed</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
